PS. Thank you Richard for the wonderful talk you gave in London! Though
one may disagree with some statements (e.g. "Install Linux if you
want a solid stable system, unless you are a kernel hacker, then you can
try our (Hurd) kernel"). I really enjoyed listening to someone who is
clearly very intelligent and fights for the righteous reason.
